*class* *classes*

*public*            accessible to any method of any class; default for members of enums or interfaces

*internal*          accessible to classes and methods of classes in the assembly (i. e. code that is to be 
                    compiled into a .exe of .dll file); default access for non-nested types in a namespace

*private*           accessible only within the containing class; not inheritable; default for a class or struct members

*protected*         accessible only within the containing class and classes derived from the containing class; inheritable private

protected *internal*  union of protected and internal, more permissible than either; accessible within 
                    the containing type, sub-type, assembly or friend assemblies (think of it as protected OR internal)

private protected   intersection of protected and internal; accessible only within the class or 
                    subclasses in the same assembly

